race.comment: MAFIA (3) proven at this grade and returned to form when second over 1280m at Muswellbrook in the Denman Cup. Will roll forward and give a great sight. ZOUNAKA (9) looked good when saluting first-up at Wyong but two runs since have been plain. Tongue-tie goes on and will appreciate the big weight drop. Ready to bounce back. OAKFIELD JUPITER (10) nice mare resuming. Made it two-straight wins before jumping in class when a tiring twelfth over 1100m in the LR Denises Joy last May. Primed with the two solid trials and will need a good ride from the draw. BROADWAY BOUNCER (2) underrated gelding with solid second-up credentials. Finally drawn a decent gate and gets his chance.
